glosses: To go after in order to catch, catch up to or find something or someone; to pursue, to give chase.
(for a road) To lead in a particular direction.
To conform to, to adhere to (another person's behavior, set of rules, teachings etc.).
To watch, to pay attention to something.
To investigate, to look into an alleged crime.
To observe a work, study etc.; to monitor.

examples.translation: You can follow us on social media!

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish تعقیب ایتمك (tʿaḳib itmek, etmek), from Arabic تَعْقِيب (taʕqīb), verbal noun of عَقَّبَ (ʕaqqaba, “to follow, to succeed”), equivalent to takip (“pursuit, follow-up”) + etmek (“to do, to make”).
